🚀 Setup Guide (Universal)

1. Requirements

You need pywal and the visualizer tools installed.

Arch/CachyOS: sudo pacman -S pywal cava cmatrix btop fastfetch fuzzel

Fedora: sudo dnf install python3-pip && pip install pywal

Debian/Ubuntu: sudo apt install python3-pip && pip install pywal

2. Clone and Install

Bash

git clone https://github.com/mhmd1233321/dark-red-noctalia.git

cd green-niri-noctalia

# Copy configs to your config directory

cp -r niri/ kitty/ fuzzel/ cava/ ~/.config/

3. Important Note

This configuration assumes you are using Niri (Wayland). If you are using a different WM (like Hyprland or Sway), you may need to adjust the autostart and window rules in the config files.
